result.description:
Adds Uber credits to a user's account. 
(Rider/Eater)

requiredArguments.name: IdempotentID
requiredArguments.description: First Half length of User UUID + Second (Half length of the Trip UUID for rides / half length of Order UUID for eats)

requiredArguments.name: Currency
requiredArguments.description: Currency Code  Eg: "USD"

requiredArguments.name: Amount
requiredArguments.description: Value to be appeased. Supports float value

requiredArguments.name: TripID
requiredArguments.description: TripID for Rides / Order for Eats

requiredArguments.name: ClientUUID
requiredArguments.description: UUID of user to whom the appeasement has to be processed

optionalArguments.name: ExpiresAt
optionalArguments.description: Indicates the expiration date and time for the credits being issued. This ensures credits are only valid within a certain period.

optionalArguments.name: Tenancy
optionalArguments.description:
Tenancy relates to the environment setting, such as 
whether the action is being performed in a testing or
production environment. "uber/testing" or "uber/production"

optionalArguments.name: CountryISO2
optionalArguments.description: countryISO2 of the user

optionalArguments.name: CityID
optionalArguments.description: city ID of the user

optionalArguments.name: Reason
optionalArguments.description: Reason for the appeasement

result.description: Adds Internal Note for the Contact

requiredArguments.name: InternalNote
requiredArguments.description:
The content of the note that is to be added internally to the 
contact.

result.description: Adds Saved Response to the Contact

requiredArguments.name: MacroID
requiredArguments.description: This is a saved reply UUID, used to add a specific saved response to the contact. Eg: "c384084c-2ab7-4d9c-b2b1-6b9e2f807cb9"

requiredArguments.name: Locale
requiredArguments.description: This parameter specifies the locale for the macro ID, ensuring that the response is appropriate for the language and regional settings. Eg: "en_US"

optionalArguments.name: DisclaimerKey
optionalArguments.description: Defines that the contact is resolved by CAR. Eg: "car.disclaimer.v1"

optionalArguments.name: contactID
optionalArguments.description: Contact ID

requiredArguments.name: RequestUUID
requiredArguments.description: A unique identifier for this payment request, ensuring each request is processed individually and no duplicates occur.

requiredArguments.name: PartnerUUID
requiredArguments.description: User ID of Driver/Earner

requiredArguments.name: Amount
requiredArguments.description: The amount to be adjusted for the partner.

requiredArguments.name: Currency
requiredArguments.description: Defines the currency code Eg: "USD"

requiredArguments.name: MiscGlobalType
requiredArguments.description:
A category or type of the miscellaneous payment. 
Eg: "Cleaning/Repair Fee"

requiredArguments.name: Description
requiredArguments.description:
Text providing more context or details about why the payment 
is being made

optionalArguments.name: TripUUID
optionalArguments.description: UUID of the Trip

requiredArguments.name: TripUUID
requiredArguments.description: UUID of the Trip

requiredArguments.name: Note
requiredArguments.description: This argument represents the content of the note you wish to add to the trip. Eg: "Fare adjustment made for cash exchange - CPM complaint"

optionalArguments.name: Tenancy
optionalArguments.description:
Tenancy relates to the environment setting, such as 
whether the action is being performed in a testing or
production environment. "uber/testing" or "uber/production"

result.description: Adds Note to the User Account

requiredArguments.name: UserUUID
requiredArguments.description: UUID of the user Eg: Eater / Rider / Earner

requiredArguments.name: Note
requiredArguments.description:
This argument contains the content of the note you wish to 
add to the user's account.

optionalArguments.name: Tenancy
optionalArguments.description:
Tenancy relates to the environment setting, such as 
whether the action is being performed in a testing or
production environment. "uber/testing" or "uber/production"

result.description: Adds tag to the User account

requiredArguments.name: UserUUID
requiredArguments.description: UUID of the user Eg: Eater / Rider / Earner

requiredArguments.name: Name
requiredArguments.description: The name of the tag to add to the user's account

requiredArguments.name: TripUUID
requiredArguments.description: UUID of the Trip

requiredArguments.name: Fare
requiredArguments.description: The new fare amount after adjustment.

requiredArguments.name: Reason
requiredArguments.description: Reason for the adjustment

optionalArguments.name: ClientMessage
optionalArguments.description: Specifies if the adjustment to be done for the rider

optionalArguments.name: DriverMessage
optionalArguments.description: Specifies if the adjustment to be done for the driver

optionalArguments.name: Tenancy
optionalArguments.description:
Tenancy relates to the environment setting, such as 
whether the action is being performed in a testing or
production environment. "uber/testing" or "uber/production"

optionalArguments.name: RefundStrategy
optionalArguments.description:
Specifies the refund method: "DEFAULT" refunds to the original
 payment method, while "UBER_CASH" refunds as Uber Credits.

requiredArguments.name: UserUUID
requiredArguments.description: UUID of the user Eg: Eater / Rider / Earner

requiredArguments.name: WorkflowUUID
requiredArguments.description: Order ID / Workflow ID

requiredArguments.name: IsGRKGFEnabled
requiredArguments.description: Boolean Value of GoldRush value

requiredArguments.name: RolloutMode
requiredArguments.description: RolloutMode of GoldRush

requiredArguments.name: ResolutionTokenEstimateUUID
requiredArguments.description: TokenID from GoldRush

requiredArguments.name: ResolutionTokenExpiresAt
requiredArguments.description: Expiry of the TokenID

requiredArguments.name: CurrencyCode
requiredArguments.description: Currency Code of the trip

requiredArguments.name: Value
requiredArguments.description: Sum total value of the base, fee and tax of the amount to be refunded. Value should be passed in e5 (amount * 100000) format

requiredArguments.name: FeeValue
requiredArguments.description: Fee value to be refunded. Value should be passed in e5 (amount * 100000) format

requiredArguments.name: TaxValue
requiredArguments.description: Tax value to be refunded. Value should be passed in e5 (amount * 100000) format

requiredArguments.name: BaseValue
requiredArguments.description: Base value to be refunded. Value should be passed in e5 (amount * 100000) format

requiredArguments.name: fareDisplay
requiredArguments.description: Total Refunded Value to be displayed to the user in the Refund acknowledgement message

requiredArguments.name: PalantirActionType
requiredArguments.description: ActionType of the Palantir. Value should be passed as "REFUND"

requiredArguments.name: IssueType
requiredArguments.description: Issue Type for the Refund

requiredArguments.name: Reason
requiredArguments.description: Reason for the Refund

requiredArguments.name: SaveResolutionOnly
requiredArguments.description: Boolean Value to disable money movement on refund for Uber Direct

requiredArguments.name: RefundType
requiredArguments.description: Type of the Refund Eg: "REFUND_TO_ORIGINAL_PAYMENT" refunds to the OPM of the order

requiredArguments.name: CountryISO2
requiredArguments.description: Country of the Order in the format of ISO2

requiredArguments.name: ShouldCheckEligibility
requiredArguments.description: Boolean Value to pass eligibility

optionalArguments.name: OrderIssueDetails
optionalArguments.description: Struct to chargeback the restaurant

result.description:
Manage order cancellations specifically for 
Uber Eats orders.

requiredArguments.name: ResolutionValue
requiredArguments.description: Returns the total value. If specified 0 meaning total value refund

requiredArguments.name: RefundPolicy
requiredArguments.description: Type of Refund Eg: "FULL_REFUND". Also takes values "PARTIAL_REFUND"

optionalArguments.name: MerchantPayPolicy
optionalArguments.description: This parameter dictates whether the merchant is compensated for the canceled order. An example value for this policy is "NO_PAY," where the merchant is not paid for the canceled order.

result.description: Updates the Status of the Contact

requiredArguments.name: Status
requiredArguments.description:
It changes the Contact's Status. Possibe values include 
"SOLVED", marks contact as Solved; "OPEN", indicating 
that the contact is still active and open to Agents; 
"ARCHIVED", for contacts to be archived; and 
"RESPONSE_REQUESTED" which requests a response 
in the agent queue.

optionalArguments.name: CurrentContactTypeID
optionalArguments.description: This parameter likely ensures alignment between the contact's current type and its status processing to maintain consistency across support actions.

result.description: Updates the Contact Type of the Contact

requiredArguments.name: ContactTypeID
requiredArguments.description: This is a unique identifier used to specify the issue type of contact. It helps in categorizing different issues users might face. Eg: "2f03cf6e-4a87-4e1c-9c14-83721914f417" for Cleaning Fee

requiredArguments.name: Path
requiredArguments.description: The path argument indicates the hierarchical path corresponding to a specific ContactTypeID. Eg: "Driver > Cleaning Fee > Requested cleaning fee" with respect to above ContactTypeID

optionalArguments.name: SuggestionID
optionalArguments.description: This ID might be used to link specific suggestions or actions to the contact context, aiding agents in providing better resolution

optionalArguments.name: AgentGroups
optionalArguments.description: A parameter indicating which agent groups are involved in handling the contact.

optionalArguments.name: SessionID
optionalArguments.description: A unique identifier for the session during which the contact type update is being made.
